+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MskUhE4Xcii9gw1e4ZsJ2Y","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete picture of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Codebase Structure Report\n\n### 1. Directory Layout\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .git/                          # Git repository\n├── .thunderdome/                  # Thunderdome (testing/validation) directory\n├── phases/                        # 12 phase requirement files\n├── src/                          # Source code directory (currently empty)\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                 # ESLint configuration\n├── .gitignore                    # Git ignore rules\n├── TASK.md                       # Main task description\n├── package.json                  # NPM dependencies and scripts\n├── package-lock.json             # Locked dependency versions\n├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript compiler configuration\n└── vitest.config.ts             # Vitest test runner configuration\n```\n\n### 2. Package.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Tsconfig.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n### 4. TASK.md Summary\n\nThe task is to build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system from scratch. The system should grow incrementally through 12 phases, each introducing new capabilities. Key points:\n\n- Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- All implementation under `src/`\n- No external runtime dependencies allowed\n- Must validate with: `npm run build` and `npm run lint`\n- Design with extensibility in mind since later phases force rethinking early decisions\n\n### 5. Complete Phase Files (1-12)\n\n**Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue**\n- Queue accepts payload and returns task object\n- Each task has unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieving next task returns oldest pending task, transitions to \"processing\"\n- Returns `null` if no tasks available\n- Must support checking how many tasks are waiting\n\n**Phase 2: Named Queues**\n- Tasks added to specific named queue\n- Default queue used if no name given\n- Each named queue operates independently\n- Implicit queue creation when first task added\n- Way to list all queue names\n- Non-existent or empty queue returns `null`\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n**Phase 3: Priority**\n- Priority levels 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest)\n- Default priority is 5\n- Higher-priority tasks returned first\n- Same priority follows FIFO order\n- Invalid priority values cause error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n**Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks**\n- Tasks can have delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not returned until availability time\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple delayed tasks: ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n- Delays work with named queues\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff**\n- Way to mark processing task as completed or failed\n- Failed task with retries re-added to queue with delay\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (1s, 2s, 4s, ...)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Default base backoff: 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Task tracks attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Task remains failed if all retries exhausted\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue**\n- Task with no retries left moves to dead letter queue\n- Way to view all dead-lettered tasks for queue\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error info and failure count\n- Can move dead-lettered task back to original queue\n- Way to clear all dead-lettered tasks\n- Each named queue has independent DLQ\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies**\n- Task can specify list of task IDs that must complete first\n- Task with unresolved dependencies is blocked\n- When dependency completes, check if blocked tasks unblocked\n- Circular dependencies detected and rejected at creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency does NOT fail dependents (stays blocked)\n- Way to inspect task's dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control**\n- Each queue has max concurrency setting\n- Limits how many tasks in processing state simultaneously\n- Returns `null` if limit reached even if pending tasks available\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: no concurrency limit (unlimited)\n- Way to set/query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Concurrency interacts correctly with priority ordering\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation**\n- Processing task can report progress as percentage (0-100) with optional message\n- Way to query task's current progress\n- Listeners can subscribe to progress updates and receive notifications\n- Subscriptions cancellable (unsubscribe)\n- Pending or processing tasks can be cancelled\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks**\n- Schedule associates cron expression with queue and task template\n- Support simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` -- every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` -- every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` -- every day at midnight\n- Way to create, remove, list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" or \"check\" mechanism evaluates all schedules\n- Recurring tasks are regular tasks after enqueue\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline**\n- Middleware functions registered per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware in order\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips task processing\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware error marks task as failed\n- Processing function/handler registered per queue\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown**\n- Shutdown signals system to stop accepting new tasks\n- New task addition after shutdown produces error\n- Shutdown waits for currently-processing tasks, up to configurable timeout\n- Non-completing tasks force-cancelled after timeout\n- Callbacks can be registered to run during shutdown\n- Shutdown produces summary (completed, force-cancelled, duration)\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe, return same result\n- Completes immediately if no processing tasks\n\n### 6. Source Code Status\n\n**Path:** `/workspace/src/`\n\nThe `src/` directory is currently empty (only contains `.gitkeep` file). All implementation needs to be created from scratch.\n\n### 7. Configuration Files\n\n**ESLint Configuration** (`/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`):\n- Uses TypeScript parser and plugin\n- Extends ESLint recommended and TypeScript recommended\n- Unused vars error with underscore pattern exceptions\n- Node.js and ES2022 environment\n\n**Vitest Configuration** (`/workspace/vitest.config.ts`):\n- Global test APIs enabled\n- 10-second test timeout\n\n**Git Ignore** (`/workspace/.gitignore`):\n- `node_modules/`\n- `dist/`\n- `*.tsbuildinfo`\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **12-phase task queue implementation project**. The codebase is a greenfield project with empty `src/` directory awaiting implementation. The system requires building an in-memory task queue similar to Bull/BeeQueue/Celery but entirely self-contained with no external runtime dependencies. \n\nThe project uses:\n- **TypeScript** (ES2022 target)\n- **Vitest** for testing\n- **ESLint** for linting\n- **Node.js** module system\n\nEach phase builds on previous functionality, requiring careful architectural planning for extensibility and backward compatibility."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa6a3d6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 22246\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 36959</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e48e9d3-8b17-4eff-a8a2-91f530d2512c","uuid":"7df3062a-2ca8-4511-9e1a-91d73b84d60d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase structure. I need to understand:\n1. The directory layout (all files and folders)\n2. The contents of package.json\n3. The contents of tsconfig.json\n4. The contents of TASK.md\n5. The contents of ALL files in the phases/ directory (phases/01.md through phases/12.md)\n6. Any existing source files in src/\n\nBe very thorough - read every phase file completely.","agentId":"aa6a3d6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete picture of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Codebase Structure Report\n\n### 1. Directory Layout\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .git/                          # Git repository\n├── .thunderdome/                  # Thunderdome (testing/validation) directory\n├── phases/                        # 12 phase requirement files\n├── 